body:
Calling `Timer.start()` after loosing focus, does not resume previously stopped task. 
To reproduce execute the example below and follow the following steps:
After the application launches, the log message ("Bug: foo") should appears every second. 
1. Press the "P" key to pause the logging task thus stopping the message from appearing. 
2. Make game window loose focus (e.g., by focusing on different window). 
3. Focus back on game window.
4. Press the "R" key to resume the stopped task.
Expected result:
The task should be resumed and the message should appear every second.
Actual result:
The task is not resumed. The message does not appear.

Tested on OS X Yosemite, with latest libgdx (1.6.1).

``` java
package com.badlogic.drop.desktop;

import com.badlogic.gdx.Game;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Gdx;
import com.badlogic.gdx.ScreenAdapter;
import com.badlogic.gdx.Input.Keys;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplication;
import com.badlogic.gdx.backends.lwjgl.LwjglApplicationConfiguration;
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Timer;
import com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Timer.Task;

public class DesktopLauncher {
    public static class BugReproduce extends Game{

        @Override
        public void create() {
            Timer.schedule(new Task() {

                @Override
                public void run() {
                    Gdx.app.log("Bug", "foo");
                }
            }, 1, 1);
            setScreen(new ScreenAdapter()); 
        }
        @Override
        public void render() {
            super.render();        
            if (Gdx.input.isKeyPressed(Keys.P)){
                Timer.instance().stop();
            }
            if (Gdx.input.isKeyPressed(Keys.R)){
                Timer.instance().start();
            }
        }
    }
    public static void main (String[] arg) {
        LwjglApplicationConfiguration config = new LwjglApplicationConfiguration();
        config.title = "BugReproduce";
        new LwjglApplication(new BugReproduce(), config);
    }
}
```
